            <h2>Our History</h2>

            <p style="text-align: justify;">With the hope and active participation from Mr Bashir Ahmed Bhuiyan, Founder and Principal of JGGHS along with the Institute’s Chairperson, Mr Khaled Chowdhury walked together with the idea of creating Trust College in the year 2005 as a cottage. But over the years, after mass response from guardians, students, participators and all prospective enterprises, we emerged as today’s Trust College in Uttara Model Town, one of the most lucrative locations of the Dhaka Metropolitan City.</p>
            <p style="text-align: justify;">At JGGHS , we provide a quality education, affiliated with the Board of Intermediate &amp; Secondary Education, Dhaka under Ministry of Education of Government of the People’s Republic of Bangladesh. Therefore, our skilled education program is directed under the National Curriculum with the medium of instruction in both Bengali and English. Here, we only promote academic learning, but we endorse the physical, spiritual and social development of each student; we do this through a stimulating environment on the board and balanced curriculum and:</p>
            <ul style="text-align: justify;">
                <li>encouraging compassion, care and respect through our shared faith and belief in the moral and mutual values.</li>
                <li>developing the pupil’s individual talents</li>
                <li>encouraging the pupils to do their best</li>
                <li>promoting family involvement in our Institute</li>
                <li>valuing each child’s individuality</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="text-align: justify;">We dream big, but we are careful to walk in little steps so that we abide by our sole policies, regulations and standards, in creating Trust College a “Center of Excellence.” We have seen our ups and downs, but never back-stepped from stepping ahead. Therefore, to promote our singular aim of modern education, we have opened the Trust College- School Section offers education from Preschool to Secondary School Certificate (SSC) level.</p>
            <p style="text-align: justify;">From the beginning of JGGHS , our  Secondary School Certificate (SSC) level students have given their best with their core talents enhanced by our sole efforts, assembled a legacy of 100% pass rate along with a mass number of A+ Grades. Here, In effect, we proudly present our first batch of students who have all succeeded in their SSC Examination 2015, letting us hold our old legacy.</p>
